        <main class="main">
            <section class="home" id="home">
                <div class="home__container container grid">
                    <img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1024/1*2IitaOv4dg7Mc4g8Ev1C6Q.jpeg" alt="NPU Chip" class="home__img">
            
                    <div class="home__data">
                        <h1 class="home__title">
                            What is an NPU?
                        </h1>
                        <p class="home__description">
                            An NPU stands for Neural Processing Unit. It is a type of specialized chip designed to handle artificial intelligence (AI) tasks, especially those related to neural networks. Unlike general-purpose processors, NPUs are built to perform many calculations simultaneously, making them ideal for tasks like image recognition and natural language processing. They help AI systems work faster and more efficiently by speeding up the computations needed for learning and decision-making.
                        </p>
                        <a href="index.html" class="button button--flex">
                            Back Home <i class="ri-arrow-right-down-line button__icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section class="about section container" id="about">
                <div class="about__container grid">
                    <img src="https://i0.wp.com/winpoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/NPU-1.jpg?fit=1024%2C1024&ssl=1" alt="NPU in Action" class="about__img">
            
                    <div class="about__data">
                        <h2 class="section__title about__title">
                            How does an NPU work?
                        </h2>
            
                        <p class="about__description">
                            An NPU works by performing many small calculations at the same time. This is different from a regular CPU, which processes tasks one at a time. NPUs have many processing units that can work together to handle the complex math needed for AI tasks. They are optimized for operations used in machine learning, such as matrix multiplications, which helps them run AI algorithms quickly and efficiently.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section class="home" id="home">
                <div class="home__container container grid">
                    <img src="https://tradingclue.kr/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/00b7a3ec-2237-4d6e-8218-b7c1102b055d.jpeg" alt="NPU vs CPU" class="home__img">
            
                    <div class="home__data">
                        <h1 class="section__title about__title">
                            What are the benefits of using an NPU?
                        </h1>
                        <br>
                        <p class="home__description">
                            NPUs offer several advantages over traditional CPUs when it comes to AI tasks. They are designed to handle the large volumes of data and complex calculations required by AI algorithms more efficiently. This means faster processing times and lower power consumption for tasks like image and speech recognition. By using NPUs, devices can perform AI tasks more quickly and with less energy, which can improve the overall performance and battery life of smart devices.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section class="about section container" id="about">
                <div class="about__container grid">
                    <img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*vbu_hPWlAC669j01CmxARA.jpeg" alt="NPU Applications" class="about__img">
            
                    <div class="about__data">
                        <h2 class="section__title about__title">
                            How are NPUs used in technology today?
                        </h2>
            
                        <p class="about__description">
                            NPUs are used in various technology applications to enhance AI capabilities. In smartphones, they help with tasks like facial recognition and image enhancement. In self-driving cars, NPUs process data from sensors to help the car understand its surroundings and make decisions. NPUs are also used in data centers to speed up AI training and inference, making large-scale machine learning projects more efficient.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
